#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:2
msgid "Instructions for the white breadboard"
msgstr "Anleitung für das weiße Breadboard"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:8
msgid "You will need:"
msgstr "Du benötigst:"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:10
msgid "A table tennis ball"
msgstr "Einen Tischtennisball"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:11
msgid "One white breadboard"
msgstr "Ein weißes Breadboard"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:12
msgid "Wires"
msgstr "Kabel"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:13
msgid "One LED with an LED holder"
msgstr "Eine LED mit LED-Halter"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:14
msgid "One wire holder"
msgstr "Einen Draht-Halter"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:15
msgid "One ESP32 development board"
msgstr "Ein ESP32-Entwicklungsboard"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:16
msgid "One 110 Ohm resistor"
msgstr "Einen 110-Ohm-Widerstand"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:19
msgid "How to proceed:"
msgstr "So gehst du vor:"

#: ../../source/white_breadboard.rst:21
msgid ""
"#. Take the tennis ball and make a small hole in it, large enough to "
"mount the LED holder. #. Connect a wire to each end of the LED. #. Insert"
" the LED holder into the hole in the tennis ball. #. Assemble the wire "
"holder with one wire of the LED attached to each end. Ensure that the "
"longer \"leg\" of the LED is connected to the ground wire. #. Mount the "
"wire holder on the breadboard. #. Locate pin number 27 on the ESP32 "
"development board. #. Plug the ESP32 development board into the "
"breadboard. #. Connect a wire from the ground pin of the ESP32 board to "
"the ground line on the breadboard. #. Insert the resistor into a free "
"space on the breadboard. #. Connect a wire from pin 27 of the ESP32 board"
" to one end of the resistor. #. Connect another wire from the other end "
"of the resistor to one side of the wire holder. #. Connect a wire from "
"the ground line on the breadboard to the other side of the wire holder. "
"#. Plug in the ESP32 development board and test the setup using Thonny. "
"For usage instructions, refer to the `Usage`__ section or continue "
"reading."
msgstr ""
"#. Bohre ein kleines Loch in den Ball, groß genug für den LED-Halter. #. "
"Verbinde an jedes LED-Bein ein Kabel. #. Setze den LED-Halter in das Loch "
"des Balls. #. Montiere den Draht-Halter und befestige je ein LED-Kabel an "
"beiden Enden. Achte darauf, dass das längere LED-Bein mit dem "
"Massekabel verbunden ist. #. Setze den Draht-Halter aufs Breadboard. #. "
"Finde Pin 27 auf dem ESP32-Board. #. Stecke das ESP32-Board ins "
"Breadboard. #. Verbinde einen Masse-Pin des ESP32 mit der Masse-Leiste "
"des Breadboards. #. Stecke den Widerstand in einen freien Platz. #. "
"Verbinde Pin 27 des ESP32 mit einem Ende des Widerstands. #. Verbinde das "
"andere Ende des Widerstands mit einer Seite des Halters. #. Verbinde die "
"Masse-Leiste des Breadboards mit der anderen Seite des Halters. #. "
"Stecke das ESP32 ein und teste den Aufbau mit Thonny. Hinweise zur "
"Nutzung findest du im Abschnitt `Usage`__ oder lies weiter."

